snippet.textDisplay:
"...specifically, an ARM-based x86 processors designed for datacenters"

...is it at all similar to those new diesel-based petrol engines? 
in all seriousness though, aren't ARM and x86 like polar opposites when it comes to CPU design philosophy? ARM is RISC (ARM literally stands for advanced RISC machine) whereas x86 is CISC which is kinda the antonym of RISC. After a bit of googling, I'm assuming this was just a typo in the script or something, because nowhere else seems to be calling this new chip both ARM and x86 based.
